Program: Discovery
Title: Gene therapy - hope to hype
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwmq
Last Broadcast Date: 18 March 1996
Has progress on the development of gene therapy stalled? The committee administering US National Institutes of Health (NIH) advice on gene therapy meets quarterly to vet applications for research grants, but its latest meeting has been cancelled. The programme asks why and looks at concern that the treatment may be promising too much. Presenter: Geoff Watts. Show less